Functions

Block of reusable code to perform a specific action.
Reusing Code

Using an existing code without writing it every time we need.
https://res.cloudinary.com/due4dmz2b/image/fetch/dpr_auto,w_auto,f_auto,q_auto/https://bss-backend-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod/media/profile_pic/card-notes-attachment/aa844695-76a0-4eef-ad78-a8184853263b.png

syntax:-
def greet():
    print("Hello")

name = input()
print(name)

Defining a Function

Function is uniquely identified by the function_name
https://res.cloudinary.com/due4dmz2b/image/fetch/dpr_auto,w_auto,f_auto,q_auto/https://bss-backend-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod/media/profile_pic/card-notes-attachment/48867533-bc9e-45e5-9d94-22a077274bbc.png

Calling a Function

The functional block of code is executed only when the function is called.
https://res.cloudinary.com/due4dmz2b/image/fetch/dpr_auto,w_auto,f_auto,q_auto/https://bss-backend-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod/media/profile_pic/card-notes-attachment/84ce001f-f30a-4f10-a5ef-d2c2faa29eae.png

def greet():
    print("Hello")

name = input()
greet()
print(name)


Defining & Calling a Function

A function should be defined before it is called.
Code

Function With Arguments

We can pass values to a function using an Argument.
https://res.cloudinary.com/due4dmz2b/image/fetch/dpr_auto,w_auto,f_auto,q_auto/https://bss-backend-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod/media/profile_pic/card-notes-attachment/2ebf11e4-d01b-4605-a6c3-4447ec7d75ac.png
def greet(word):
    msg = "Hello " + word
    print(msg)

name = input()
greet(word=name)


Variables Inside a Function

A variable created inside a function can only be used in it.
Code
def greet(word):
    msg = "Hello " + word

name = input()
greet(word=name)
print(msg)

output:-NameError: name 'msg' is not defined

Returning a Value

To return a value from the function use return
 keyword.
https://res.cloudinary.com/due4dmz2b/image/fetch/dpr_auto,w_auto,f_auto,q_auto/https://bss-backend-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod/media/profile_pic/card-notes-attachment/e951094a-3007-4bff-b2b8-2ce521dc72e7.png

Exits from the function when return statement is executed.
Code

def greet(word):
    msg = "Hello " + word
    return msg

name = input()
greeting = greet(word=name)
print(greeting)

Code written after return statement will not be executed.
def greet(word):
    msg = "Hello "+word
    return msg
    print(msg)

name = input()
greeting = greet(word=name)
print(greeting)

Built-in Functions

We are already using functions which are pre-defined in Python.
Built-in functions are readily available for reuse

    print()
    int()
    str()
    len()





